                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-353-off1818 t18300916-353-crimeloc1821"></join>. On the 24th of September, about twenty-five minutes past ten o'clock, I had four hats hanging at the door - I left a boy in the shop, who went to sleep; a witness gave an alarm, I ran out, and pursued the prisoner, who was secured by a Policeman.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-353-person2871">
                  WILLIAM 
                  SCARDFIELD
               <interp inst="t18300916-353-person2871" type="surname" value="SCARDFIELD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-353-person2871" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-353-person2871" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I saw the prisoner take a hat from the door, put it on his head, and run off; he had no hat of his own - I gave an alarm, and am sure he is the man.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-353-person2872">
                  DANIEL 
                  RIERDON
               <interp inst="t18300916-353-person2872" type="surname" value="RIERDON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-353-person2872" type="given" value="DANIEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-353-person2872" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I stopped the prisoner in Broadway soon after this happened, and took the hat off his head.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was standing at the corner of Broadway - a young man, whom I frequently drank with, came up intoxicated; I was looking at a quarrel in the street - he pulled this hat off his head, took a cap out of it, and began swearing; I said, "What is the matter?" he said, "I have bought a hat, and wish I had not bought it, for I want the money more;" I bought it of him for 5s. 6d., and had not had it on five minutes before I was taken. <rs id="t18300916-353-verdict1822" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18300916-353-verdict1822" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 24.</p>
